#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.80"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.80:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.80:0.2"
msgid "8. Gilānavagga"
msgstr "8. Sick"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 80. Dutiyaavijjāpahānasutta → dutiyaavijjāsuttaṃ (bj) | avijjā 2 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.80:0.3"
msgid "80. Dutiyaavijjāpahānasutta"
msgstr "80. Giving Up Ignorance"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.80:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu … pe … etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn35.80:1.2"
msgid ""
"“atthi nu kho, bhante, eko dhammo yassa pahānā bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, "
"vijjā uppajjatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, is there one thing such that by giving it up a mendicant gives up "
"ignorance and gives rise to knowledge?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.80:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Atthi kho, bhikkhu, eko dhammo yassa pahānā bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, "
"vijjā uppajjatī”ti."
msgstr "“There is, mendicant.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.80:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Katamo pana, bhante, eko dhammo yassa pahānā bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, "
"vijjā uppajjatī”ti?"
msgstr "“But what is that one thing?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.80:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Avijjā kho, bhikkhu, eko dhammo yassa pahānā bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, "
"vijjā uppajjatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Ignorance is one thing such that by giving it up a mendicant gives up "
"ignorance and gives rise to knowledge.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.80:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Kathaṃ pana, bhante, jānato, kathaṃ passato avijjā pahīyati, vijjā "
"uppajjatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But how does a mendicant know and see so as to give up ignorance and give "
"rise to knowledge?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.80:6.1"
msgid "“Idha, bhikkhu, bhikkhuno sutaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "“It’s when a mendicant has heard:"

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.2"
msgid "‘sabbe dhammā nālaṃ abhinivesāyā’ti."
msgstr "‘Nothing is worth clinging on to.’"

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.3"
msgid "Evañcetaṃ, bhikkhu, bhikkhuno sutaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "When a mendicant has heard that"

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.4"
msgid "‘sabbe dhammā nālaṃ abhinivesāyā’ti."
msgstr "nothing is worth clinging on to,"

# Surely annato here is equivalent to parato, contra BB.
msgctxt "sn35.80:6.5"
msgid ""
"So sabbaṃ dhammaṃ abhijānāti, sabbaṃ dhammaṃ abhiññāya sabbaṃ dhammaṃ "
"parijānāti, sabbaṃ dhammaṃ pariññāya sabbanimittāni aññato passati, cakkhuṃ "
"aññato passati, rūpe …"
msgstr ""
"they directly know all things. Directly knowing all things, they completely "
"understand all things. Completely understanding all things, they see all "
"signs as other. They see the eye, sights,"

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.6"
msgid "cakkhuviññāṇaṃ …"
msgstr "eye consciousness,"

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.7"
msgid "cakkhusamphassaṃ …"
msgstr "and eye contact as other."

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.8"
msgid ""
"yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā "
"adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi aññato passati … pe …"
msgstr ""
"And they also see the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises "
"conditioned by eye contact as other. …"

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.9"
msgid "manaṃ aññato passati, dhamme …"
msgstr "They see the mind, thoughts,"

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.10"
msgid "manoviññāṇaṃ …"
msgstr "mind consciousness,"

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.11"
msgid "manosamphassaṃ …"
msgstr "and mind contact as other."

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.12"
msgid ""
"yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā "
"adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi aññato passati."
msgstr ""
"And they also see the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises "
"conditioned by mind contact as other."

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.13"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, jānato evaṃ passato bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, vijjā "
"uppajjatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant knows and sees so as to give up ignorance and give "
"rise to knowledge.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.80:6.14"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
